Source: I004 and `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-17-visible-quota-configuration.md`, Task 1.

Create the pure `VisibleQuotaConfig` compatibility core with opaque `specFor(profile, persisted)` and immutable `apply(windows, spec)`. Move exact persisted-shape, strict/sparse default, dynamic-window, and OpenCode identity semantics behind the seam; refocus `tests/test-visibility.mjs` on that interface.

Acceptance: execution preflight proves I001/I003 done and the post-I002 loader/post-I003 registry seam exist; every valid legacy/global/per-provider format retains runtime meaning; every provider/OpenCode identity path is characterised; dynamic unknown IDs honour exact overrides or `defaultVisible`; application clones without mutation, preserves order/duplicates, ignores stale incoming `visible`, treats deliberately foreign opaque specs as defaults without inspection, handles malformed input safely, and baseline visibility behaviours pass.
